    ["description"] = "After the unsuccessful attempt to build a one-nation state a country in Caucasus has lost some of its territories where people didn’t want to be called “inferior”, “inadequate” or “nonexistent”. At the forefront of separatist movement was the area from Pitsunda to Senaki. People started to call their land “Republic”. An attempt to return this territory by force turned into lengthy and bloody war, both sides suffered severe losses and Republic has lost city Senaki. The population of Republic called the enemy “butchers” for the multitude of war crimes they committed.\
\
Two weeks ago the enemy started another attempt to “reestablish constitutional order” in the Republic. No side had the upper hand over the other however the “butchers” had better equipment. \
\
One mixed brigade consisting of one tank and two motorized battalions with support of GRAD rocket artillery and at least four Su-25 and two Mi-24 was up against the Republic. The republic only had transport helicopters and two Mi-8’s. An attempt to equip Mi-8 with rocket pods and use them in combat resulted in one of them being practically sawed in half by the enemy BMP-2. \
\
Naturally the Main HQ refrained from further such attempts and started looking for other ways to strengthen its small army. The help came from the neighbor to the north who’s parliament has recently recognized Republic as a sovereign nation. This now allowed for weapons to be supplied legally (sort of). \
\
As a result an arms deal was quickly set up where Republic’s Air Forces have received a used Ka-50 helicopter in a very good condition. Moreover a pilot, fairly young man who recently retired from service, was found up north who was willing to fly and fight on the Ka-50. \
\
I am a mercenary, imagine that! Well, not exactly a mercenary, more like a volunteer fighter. After all there is are now formal diplomatic relationships between my country and Republic and most of the population there have dual citizenships. \
\
Still, I could never imagine that after retiring I will ever fly and fight again. And here I am, sitting in the cargo bay of Ilushin with my new bird, yes it is basically mine now! And the beautiful bird it is! I could only dream about flying something like this. \
\
From my early days in service I always kept my ears open for any news about Ka-50, I kept magazine articles about it and anxiously watched video reports. And I even saw it once in flesh, when a pair of them came to us in Chechnya for combat trials. Could I ever imagine back then that one day I will be standing beside one, touching its cold black armor, feeling its might and power. \
\
Every man, deep down, and sometimes right on the surface, has a soft spot for a weapon, be it old knife or a brand new rifle, heavy tank or a swift jet fighter. And now I got myself the most beautiful attack helicopter. Looking at it from the left side one can think it is a purely peaceful machine if one forgets that on the right side it has a powerful cannon and at the back of cargo bay there are detached wings with hardpoints for some more serious arguments. They called it Werevolf for a reason! \
\
Well, let’s show them that even one can make a difference.",
